&lt;h3&gt;The opportunity:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Lead QA Engineer to be the technical authority on complex accounts. This is a hands-on technical leadership role—you&#39;ll architect automation frameworks, solve the hard problems, and set the technical direction for QA on your engagements, as well as being an active member of the QA community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re the person the team turns to when things get complicated. You&#39;ve built automation from the ground up, you understand the trade-offs, and you know how to design solutions that scale. You lead through expertise—raising the bar technically and helping others grow through mentorship and demonstration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re also an innovator. You&#39;re actively using AI tools to accelerate your work and you&#39;re thinking about what&#39;s next—whether that&#39;s self-healing tests, smarter automation, or new approaches to quality. You don&#39;t just follow best practice; you help shape it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And beyond the technical, you&#39;re a confident communicator who can hold your own with senior client stakeholders—explaining approaches, trade-offs, and recommendations to influence decisions at a project level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the technical lead for QA on complex engagements—owning test strategy and the automation approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect, build, and evolve automation frameworks that others can rely on and contribute to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and solve the hard technical problems—test architecture, flaky tests, CI/CD integration, environment issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the technical direction for QA on your accounts—tooling, approach, and structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive shift-left practices, embedding quality into requirements, design, and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute test strategies across UI, functional, integration, API, accessibility and regression testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and elevate QA engineers through hands-on collaboration and knowledge sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate with AI—using modern tools to work smarter and exploring what&#39;s next for QA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical recommendations and trade-offs to clients and internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in client-facing forums—demos, triage, release calls, and technical discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a specialism and share knowledge across the wider QA community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What we want from you:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear track record in automation architecture and technical problem-solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid experience testing in complex, transactional environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Playwright and TypeScript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve designed frameworks from scratch—not just written tests, but built the foundations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working across the full stack—Web apps, Native Apps, APIs, backends, logs, data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ha

